The paper deals with the design of a coding scheme for MIMO fading systems with channel output and channel state feedback at the transmitter. This involves the use of information theory (cs.IT) to achieve any rate up to capacity, as well as networked systems (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY) to handle the feedback. The paper also discusses linear processing schemes (cs.MM) and the use of limited rate feedback channels (cs.COM) to convey quantized CSI.
